article.headline: Drake 77, Indiana State 68 (OT)
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Sean Tracy hit three free throws in the final seconds of overtime to secure a 77-68 victory for Drake over Indiana State Wednesday night in a Missouri Valley Conference game. The three points were Tracy's only scores for the game as six Drake players scored in beating Indiana State 15-6 during the overtime period. Nick Grant led Drake (11-8, 4-4 MVC) with 15 points and Al Stewart and Jonathan Cox both scored 13 as Cox also grabbed 12 rebounds. Chris Bryant added 11 points and Ajay Calvin had 10 as the Bulldogs beat Indiana State for the second time in a week. The Sycamores (8-8, 1-7) led 59-54 before Drake went on an 8-0 run to take a three-point lead with 1:39 left in regulation. Indiana State's Tyson Schnitker, who scored 22 points for the game, hit a jumper and Gabriel Moore hit the second of two free throws to tie the game at 62 going into overtime. The loss was the eighth straight for Indiana State after opening the season with eight victories. Other top scorers for Indiana State were Moore with 13 points, Jay Tunnell with 12 and Jeremiah Wise with 10.
